.TH "fsverity_prepare_hash_state" 9 "fsverity_prepare_hash_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsverity_prepare_hash_state \- precompute the initial hash state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const u8 *" fsverity_prepare_hash_state
.BI "(struct fsverity_hash_alg *alg "  ","
.BI "const u8 *salt "  ","
.BI "size_t salt_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "alg" 12
hash algorithm
.IP "salt" 12
a salt which is to be prepended to all data to be hashed
.IP "salt_size" 12
salt size in bytes, possibly 0
.SH "RETURN"
NULL if the salt is empty, otherwise the \fBkmalloc\fP'ed precomputed
initial hash state on success or an \fBERR_PTR\fP on failure.
